data.title: Tom Cruise
data.meta_description: A Big Star With A Complex Personal Life
data.text:
Tom Cruise poses with British actress Emily Blunt at the premiere of the film "Edge of Tomorrow" in Paris on May 28, 2014.

Tom Cruise

Tom Cruise speaks onstage during The State of the Industry: Past, Present and Future and Paramount Pictures Presentation at The Colosseum at Caesars Palace during CinemaCon, the official convention of the National Association of Theatre Owners, on April, 21, 2015, in Las Vegas, Nevada.

Tom Cruise

Tom Cruise and Jimmy Fallon play "Egg Roulette" during a taping of "Late Night With Jimmy Fallon" at Rockefeller Center on April 12, 2013, in New York.

Tom Cruise

Tom Cruise attends the world premiere of "Jack Reacher" at Odeon Leicester Square on December 10, 2012, in London.

Tom Cruise

Actors Tom Cruise at the premiere of "Super 8" on June 8, 2011 in Westwood, Calif.

Tom Cruise

Cruise, left, kisses Katie Holmes as the newly-engaged couple visits the old port of Marseille, southern France, June 17, 2005. Cruise popped the question at the Eiffel Tower early that the morning, then announced the news during a press conference for his film "War of the Worlds."

Tom Cruise

Tom Cruise perform at the MTV movie awards in Los Angeles on June 6, 2010.

Tom Cruise

Actor Tom Cruise, right, stands in the pits with NASCAR team owner Rick Hendrick, just before the start of Sunday's NASCAR Sprint Cup Series Pep Boys Auto 500 at Atlanta Motor Speedway. Cruise, who has become a familiar face at NASCAR races this season, will narrate a documentary about Hendrick.

Tom Cruise

Katie Holmes, pictured here with husband Tom Cruise and daughter Suri, on the eve of her wedding in Rome in November of 2006.

Tom Cruise

Cruise and actress Katie Holmes laugh as they oblige photographers' requests for a kiss, as they arrive at the St. Cecilia auditorium for the David di Donatello Italian film awards, in Rome, April 29, 2005. Two days earlier, representative for both Cruise, 42, and Holmes, 26, confirmed the pair had been dating for a few weeks.

Tom Cruise

Actor Tom Cruise escorts his wife, actress Katie Holmes, into the Metropolitan Museum of Art's Costume Institute Gala, in New York on Monday, May 5, 2008.

Tom Cruise

Tom Cruise lifts Penelope Cruz as they arrive for the British premiere of his film "The Last Samurai," Jan. 6, 2004, at the Odeon Leicester Square, central London. The couple announced the end of their relationship in March 2004.

Tom Cruise

Actor Tom Cruise attends the premiere of his film "The Last Samurai," at the Ziegfeld Theater, Dec. 2, 2003, in New York. One of Hollywood's most bankable stars, Cruise gained fame as a heartthrob in such movies as "Risky Business" and "Top Gun," solidified his dramatic credentials in "Rain Man" and won a Best Actor Oscar nomination for "Born on The Fourth of July."

Tom Cruise

Cruise escorts his date Mimi Rogers at the premiere of the film "The Color of Money," in Los Angeles, Oct. 14, 1986. The couple married in 1987 and divorced three years later.

Tom Cruise

Cruise, second from left, poses with "The Color of Money" castmembers Paul Newman, left, and Mary Elizabeth Mastrantonio, and director Martin Scorsese, Oct. 18, 1986.

Tom Cruise

Cruise, right, and Dustin Hoffman appear in a scene from the 1988 film "Rain Man."

Tom Cruise

Cruise is photographed with Nicole Kidman in 1993. Kidman and Cruise were wed on Christmas Eve, 1990, in a secret ceremony after meeting on the set of "Days of Thunder." They also starred in "Far and Away" and Stanley Kubrick's final film, the sexual thriller "Eyes Wide Shut." The couple, who have two adopted children, surprised celebrity-watchers in announcing the end of the relationship in 2001.

Tom Cruise

Cruise shields his eyes from the glare as he takes a question during a press conference in Hamburg, Germany, June 16, 1996, about his movie "Mission: Impossible."

Tom Cruise

Cruise and Kidman arrive for the 69th Annual Academy Awards at the Shrine Auditorium in Los Angeles, March 24, 1997.

Tom Cruise

Cruise, foreground, and Kidman arrive at Westminster Abbey with fellow actor Tom Hanks, left, and director Steven Spielberg, for the funeral of Diana, Princess of Wales, Sept. 6, 1997. Shortly after Diana's death Cruise blasted the paparazzi in a television interview, and said he'd been chased in the same tunnel where she crashed.

Tom Cruise

Cruise speaks to the media outside London's High Court, Oct. 29, 1998. He and Kidman had accepted undisclosed, substantial libel damages over allegations that their marriage was a hypocritical sham to cover up their alleged homosexuality.

Tom Cruise

Cruise and Kidman kiss at the end of a press conference unveiling their movie "Eyes Wide Shut" by late film director Stanley Kubrick, at the 56th Venice Film Festival in Venice, Italy, Sept. 1, 1999.

Tom Cruise

Cruise, executive producer of the film "The Others," engages in a playful head lock with fellow executive producer Harvey Weinstein during a special screening of the film in Los Angeles, Aug. 7, 2001.

Tom Cruise

Cruise arrives with his mother, Mary South, for the 61st Annual Golden Globe Awards in Beverly Hills, Calif. Jan. 25, 2004. Cruise was nominated for Best Performance by an Actor in a Motion Picture for his work in "The Last Samurai"; the award went to Sean Penn.

Tom Cruise

Actor Tom Cruise, center, and his mother, Mary Lee Mapother, arrive at the 66th Annual Golden Globe Awards on Sunday, Jan. 11, 2009, in Beverly Hills, Calif.

Tom Cruise

Cruise and Spanish actress Penelope Cruz, front, are joined by Sylvester Stallone, back left, and Reba McEntire, back right, and other entertainers on the phone bank during "America: A Tribute to Heroes" telethon, Sept. 21, 2001, to raise money for victims of the Sept. 11 attacks.

Tom Cruise

Cruise, left, director Cameron Crowe and Cruz pose for the camera following a press conference promoting their film "Vanilla Sky" in Toronto, Dec. 5, 2001. Cruise and Cruz met on the set of the film and were a couple for three years.
